<subSubSection id="FA9AB2FAFFB36651C6ACE4163378FCF9" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B23FE171FFB36651C6ACE41637DDF891" blockId="4.[158,801,1537,1977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C6ACE4163671F991" bold="true" box="[158,276,1538,1561]" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C729E4153696F991" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Etzel" authorityYear="2001" box="[283,499,1537,1561]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="raddai">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C729E4153696F991" box="[283,499,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">Cnesterodon raddai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed by the following autapomorphies: (1) the small number (one to four) of patches of dark pigmentation along flanks; (2) minute size of adults; (3) predorsal line absent; (4) three pelvic-fin rays in males [33-3]. 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C71CE4953564F911" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Etzel" authorityYear="2001" box="[302,513,1665,1689]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="raddai">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C71CE4953564F911" box="[302,513,1665,1689]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">Cnesterodon raddai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
further differs from its congeners by: (1) pleural ribs in adult males not curved forward converging to the same point towards pelvic girdle [59-0]; and (2) anterior and posterior orbital bony plates present [143- 1].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B23FE171FFB36651C6F6E5363378FCF9" blockId="4.[158,801,1537,1977]" lastBlockId="4.[839,1482,730,881]" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">
In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C77BE53636D4F8B1" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Etzel" authorityYear="2001" box="[329,433,1825,1849]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="raddai">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C77BE53636D4F8B1" box="[329,433,1825,1849]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">C. raddai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from its congeners, but 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C53AE5363641F8D1" authorityName="Lucinda &amp; Garavello" authorityYear="2001" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omorgmatos">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C53AE536347FF8B1" box="[776,794,1826,1849]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C6ACE5563641F8D1" box="[158,292,1858,1881]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">omorgmatos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the circular or irregular dark brown blotches along body sides. 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C752E575355DF8F1" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Etzel" authorityYear="2001" box="[352,568,1889,1913]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="raddai">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C752E575355DF8F1" box="[352,568,1889,1913]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">Cnesterodon raddai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C6ACE5963620F811" authorityName="Lucinda &amp; Garavello" authorityYear="2001" box="[158,325,1922,1945]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omorgmatos">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C6ACE59637D5F811" box="[158,176,1922,1945]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C68CE5963620F811" box="[190,325,1922,1945]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">omorgmatos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the general size of adults (14.6-17.0 mm [adult males], 17.1-23.2 mm [adult females] 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C45EE5B635E7F831" box="[620,642,1954,1977]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">vs</emphasis>
. 18.7-24.8 mm [adult males], 20.0-30.5 mm [adult females], respectively) and by its color pattern (one to four clearly rounded dark spots or wide and short bars along flanks 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C29DE10E33A0FCB9" box="[1199,1221,794,817]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">vs</emphasis>
. six to nine dark brown circular to irregular blotches or vertical wide bars along body sides, respectively).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA9AB2FAFFB36651C575E18E33A1FBC7" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B23FE171FFB36651C575E18E3266FC59" blockId="4.[839,1481,921,977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C575E18E34BEFC39" bold="true" box="[839,987,922,945]" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C5D6E18D33DAFC39" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Etzel" authorityYear="2001" box="[996,1215,921,945]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="raddai">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C5D6E18D33DAFC39" box="[996,1215,921,945]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">Cnesterodon raddai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the rio 
<collectingCountry id="CA97A1E1FFB36651C575E1AE34CEFC59" box="[839,939,954,977]" name="Paraguay" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and lower rio Paraná drainages.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B23FE171FFB36651C575E1EC33A1FBC7" blockId="4.[839,1481,1016,1103]" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C575E1EC32FDFBB8" bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C575E1EC3341FB98" authorityName="Lucinda" authorityYear="2005" box="[839,1060,1016,1040]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="iguape">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C575E1EC3341FB98" bold="true" box="[839,1060,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">Cnesterodon iguape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C20DE1EC3354FBB8" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C20DE1EC33B2FB98" authorityName="Lucinda &amp; Garavello" authorityYear="2001" box="[1087,1239,1016,1040]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hypselurus">C. hypselurus</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C2C0E1EC32D1FB98" box="[1266,1460,1016,1040]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">C. septentrionalis</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C54AE60C3354FBB8" box="[888,1073,1048,1072]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevirostratus">C. brevirostratus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C27FE60C33B6FBB8" authorityName=", Haseman" authorityYear="1911" box="[1101,1235,1048,1072]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="carnegiei">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C27FE60C33B6FBB8" bold="true" box="[1101,1235,1048,1072]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">C. carnegiei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="75809AF2FFB36651C2DDE60C32FDFBB8" authorityName="Lucinda &amp; Garavello" authorityYear="2001" box="[1263,1432,1048,1072]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Cnesterodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omorgmatos">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C2DDE60C32FDFBB8" bold="true" box="[1263,1432,1048,1072]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">C. omorgmatos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Clade [103]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA9AB2FAFFB36651C575E66A33DCFA1D" pageId="4" pageNumber="263" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B23FE171FFB36651C575E66A33CEFB5D" blockId="4.[839,1482,1150,1429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="80F43D63FFB36651C575E66A34DDFB1D" bold="true" box="[839,952,1150,1173]" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Members of this clade share the following uniquely derived and unreversed feature: constriction of unpaired appendix of gonopodium [103-1**].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B23FE171FFB36651C55EE6CA33DCFA1D" blockId="4.[839,1482,1150,1429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">
Additionally, this clade is diagnosed by the following not uniquely derived and/or reversed features: (1) medial surface of ascending process of premaxilla approximately straight [11- 0]; (2) teeth on fourth ceratobranchial [27-0]; (3) first proximal radial of dorsal fin located between neural spines of 13 
<superScript id="45F54C39FFB36651C3A2E74832F9FAE2" attach="left" box="[1424,1436,1372,1386]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">th</superScript>
and 14 
<superScript id="45F54C39FFB36651C553E7683408FA02" attach="left" box="[865,877,1404,1418]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="263">th</superScript>
vertebrae in adult males [62-1].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
